content:
Multi Auto Rating Procedure

A rating is a risk-based calculation of a premium based on a set of input characteristics. You'll set up, map, and implement rating procedures for all your products and plans.

The Multi Auto rating procedure rates drivers and vehicles by calling calculation procedures. To rate the Multi Auto insurance product, we use an Integration procedure:

Type: Auto
Subtype: MultiInstanceRating
Name: Auto+MultiDriver Rating

This Integration Procedure orchestrates two major rating calculations - driver and vehicle calculations. While you'll create your own integration procedure to rate your auto insurance products, you can look at and test out the structure of this one.

Here's what component each step of the procedure uses:

Calculation Action:
  Rates drivers by calling the calculation procedure.
  Rates vehicles by calling the calculation procedure.

List Action:
  Merges calculation results for drivers with original input data.

Calculation Action:
  Rates vehicles by calling the calculation procedure.

Response Action:
  Returns response for the vehicle calculation action.

The Multi Auto rating procedure uses calculation procedures to perform calculations on matrix lookups and user-defined variables and constants. It calls these calculation procedures:

autoRateDrivers
autoRateVehicles
title: Understanding Multi Auto Rating Procedure
